          <p class="sw-section-heading">What you're seeing from above</p>
          <p>Let me describe what the aerial view shows:</p>
          <ul class="sw-list"><li><strong>An Egyptian obelisk </strong>standing at the dead center</li><li><strong>An eight-pointed star </strong>radiating outward from the obelisk, formed by lines of dark stone in the pavement</li><li><strong>Four circular rings </strong>around the obelisk with sixteen lines extending out like a giant sunburst</li><li><strong>Two massive curved colonnades </strong>(Bernini's 284 columns) sweeping around the plaza like two arms embracing the center</li><li><strong>Zodiacal markers </strong>in the pavement that track the obelisk's shadow through the year like a giant sundial</li></ul>
          <p>This is the geometric design of the most important public space in Roman Catholicism. <strong>It is, from above, an astronomical diagram and a pagan ritual symbol.</strong> Billions of Catholics have walked across it. Popes have been elected above it. World leaders have made pilgrimage to it. And almost nobody has ever looked at it from the sky.</p>
      </div>
